              formula. OBJECTIVE: To examine the associations of delivery mode
              and feeding method with infant intestinal microbiome composition
              at approximately 6 weeks of life. DESIGN, SETTING, AND
              PARTICIPANTS: Prospective observational study of 102 infants
              followed up as part of a US pregnancy cohort study. EXPOSURES:
              Delivery mode was abstracted from delivery medical records, and
              feeding method prior to the time of stool collection was
              ascertained through detailed questionnaires. MAIN OUTCOMES AND
              MEASURES: Stool microbiome composition was characterized using
              next-generation sequencing of the 16S rRNA gene. RESULTS: There
              were 102 infants (mean gestational age, 39.7 weeks; range,
