              associated with exclusive formula feeding than exclusive
              breastfeeding (P = .002). We identified 6 individual bacterial
              genera that were differentially abundant between delivery mode and
              feeding groups. CONCLUSIONS AND RELEVANCE: The infant intestinal
              microbiome at approximately 6 weeks of age is significantly
              associated with both delivery mode and feeding method, and the
              supplementation of breast milk feeding with formula is associated
              with a microbiome composition that resembles that of infants who
